<p>&#8216;The statutory power of advancement conferred by section 32 of the Trustee Act 1925 is a valuable tool for trustees given them as an aid to enable trust property to be used for the fullest benefit of a beneficiary with an interest in capital: see Lord Inglewood v IRC [1983] 1 WLR 366, 372â€“3 per Fox LJ, a judgment which contains a useful catalogue of ways in which the power has been exercised.&#8217;</p>
